<h1>About</h1>
<div class="intro">
  <p>I'm Mari. I'm a staff software engineer at Netflix, where I work on consumer identity — the systems that know which device is yours, which session to end, which of two hundred million accounts just signed in. I've been writing software for fifteen years and poems for longer, in two languages <span class="es">(a veces en las dos a la vez)</span>.</p>
  <p><span class="es">Cuba → Uruguay → United States.</span> I'm a software engineer by trade, an entrepreneur by life school, (grand)daughter, friend. In my free time I write poems and short stories. I tend to write short essays and like conciseness.</p>
  <p>I learn by building, so most of what lives here is something you can read, run, or play with: essays on <span class="tech">debugging</span> and <span class="tech">distributed&nbsp;systems</span>, explorable simulations, poems, stories, talks.</p>
  <p>For more technical writing, find me at <a href="https://mlescaille.medium.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">mlescaille on Medium<span class="external-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>.</p>
</div>
</Base>
